14... a5
{ 14...Kh8  was inspired by Giri-Carlsen ½-½ 2019.  15.Ncb4  Nxb4  16.Nxb4  Qb6  17.a4  bxa4  18.Qxa4  Bb7  19.Nxa6  Bxa6  20.Qxa6  Qxb2  21.Ra2  Qxc3  22.Qxd6  Rfd8  23.Qa3  Qd4  24.Qa7  f6  25.Qxd4  Rxd4  26.Bf3  g6  27.g3  Rb7  28.Kg2  Kg7  29.h4  Bh6  30.Rfa1  Rdb4  ½-½ Tomashevskaya-Gueci, Skopje 2019. }
15. Qd3 Ne7 { A key idea: eliminate the knight in the outpost. } 16. Nce3 Be6
17. Rad1
{ Similar to  17.Rfd1  , but it is hard to see a shining future for the rook  on f1. }
17... Nxd5 18. Nxd5 g6
{ One of the many possibilities in a dynamically balanced position. Black is improving the kingside while we already have a lot of space on the queenside. Don't forget about the typical maneuver ...Bd8-b6, especially in an opposite-colored bishop kind of position. }
