{ Usually, in the Sveshnikov Sicilian Black has a minority on the queenside and must know how to play with it. When a4 is played, White wants to open the a-file for the rook, so Black captures and tries to exploit the semi-open b-file. }
1... bxa4 2. Ncb4 Nxb4 3. cxb4 Bb7
{ Black opens the position for the bishop pair and is ready to start the dynamic with ...Qc8 and ...Bxd5. }
