15. Qxf6 gxf6
{ Both players have three pawn islands and the position is balanced. } 16. Rad1
Bf5 17. Bb3 Rd7
{ I prefer Black because we can attack White's weaknesses. Moreover, Black is quicker in the fight for the d-file. There's no way to exploit the doubled pawns on f6 and f7. }
