1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 e5
{ This is the starting position of the Sveshnikov Sicilian. We are going to study now White's alternatives on move six. While in other Sicilian lines, such as the Najdorf, White has different options on the 6th move to fight for a slight advantage, in the Sveshnikov, the other lines besides the standard  6.Ndb5  , don't give Black any theoretical difficulty. These moves are all quite rare, and in my classic games, I've only experienced  6.Nde2  . }
6. Nxc6
{ White moves the knight for the third time and gives Black the domination of d5. It is preferable to take on c6 with the b-pawn, following the principle of 'capture toward the center'. }
6... bxc6
{ Black has already solved the problems with the d5-square, and with one more defender, it will be easier to achieve the ...d5 break. The structure on the queenside may look weak, but White doesn't have a straightforward way to attack it. Moreover, by capturing on c6, Black can exploit the semi-open b-file. }
7. Bg5
{ With the pawn on c6, this move is useless. Now, Black can immediately target b2 by playing ...Rb8. }
7... Rb8 8. Rb1 h6 9. Bh4 Qa5
{ Pinning the knight and threatening both ...Rxb2 and ...Nxe4. } 10. Bxf6 Rxb2
{ White reckoned only one threat, so it's time for the other one! } 11. Kd2
{ We have an extra pawn, the bishop on f6 is hanging, and ...Bb4 is almost unstoppable. Black's position is crushing.   11.Bxe5  Qxe5–+  , and if @@StartFEN@@2b1kb1r/p2p1pp1/2p2B1p/q3p3/4P3/2N5/PrP2PPP/1R1QKB1R w Kk - 0 11@@EndFEN@@  11.Rxb2  Qxc3+  12.Qd2  Qxb2–+  . }
11... Bb4
{ The most elegant choice, bringing another piece to the party! Now it's impossible to save both the knight on c3 and the bishop on f6. }
12. Rxb2 Bxc3+ 13. Ke2 Qa4
{ ...Qxe4# is coming, so White can save neither the rook nor bishop. Don't worry, the human  13...Bxb2–+  works well too. }
14. f3 Bxb2 15. Bxg7 Ba6+ { The material is equal, but Black's king is safer. }
16. Ke1 Qa5+ 17. Kf2 Bd4+ 18. Kg3 Rg8
{ Winning the bishop on g7 and the game. } *

