{ It looks like White won the fight for the d5-square but cannot occupy it with a good piece without a pair of knights on the board. The knight on b3 is geometrically on the worst square to go to d5. }
12. Bd5 Ne7
{ Black is statically better because of the pawn structure, and dynamically because of the piece activity. Attacking the weakness on c3 with ...Rac8 will be easy, and then playing on the kingside with ...Ng6-f4. }
