6... d6
{ 6...h6  was played many times by the legendary GM Ulf Andersson.  Black allows the entry of the knight on d6.  7.Nd6+  Bxd6  8.Qxd6  Qe7  . How could one of the most famous strategists invent this line? The position seems terrible for Black; he gave up the bishop pair and will enter an endgame with the king  on e7. Even if I don't like it, it's perfectly playable.    9.Qxe7+  Kxe7  10.b3  d6  11.Ba3  a6  12.O-O-O  Rd8  13.Bc4  Be6  14.Bd5  Rac8  15.Kb2  b5  16.Bxc6  Rxc6  17.Rd3  Rb8  18.Nd5+  Bxd5  19.exd5  Rcc8  20.Bb4  Ra8  21.Ba5  g5  22.Re1  Nd7  23.h4  g4  24.f4  gxf3  25.gxf3  Rg8  26.f4  Rac8  27.fxe5  Nxe5  28.Bc3  f6  29.Re4  h5  30.Rd2  Rg4  31.Rde2  Rc5  32.Bxe5  dxe5  33.c4  bxc4  34.bxc4  Rxc4  35.Rxc4  Rxc4  0-1 Berg-Andersson, Katrineholm 1999. }
