{ White's only alternative to fight for equality, trying to remove the defender of the strong knight on d5. Now Black must find an essential intermediate move. }
18... Nc3 { Only move. } 19. Qf3 Bxc4 20. Nxc4
{ A critical moment. Is Qxc3 a threat or not? Luckily for Black, it isn't! }
20... b5 { Counterattacking the opponent's knight. } 21. axb5 axb5 22. Qxc3 Bd4
23. Qg3
{ More or less the same position as @@StartFEN@@2r2rk1/2q2ppp/p7/1pb1pP2/P1N5/1Pn2Q2/2P3PP/R1B2R1K w - b6 0 21@@EndFEN@@  21.Qxc3  with the opening of the a-file included. }
