13... Nd7 14. Kh1
{ This mysterious king move prevents ...Bf6 because after fxe5, the pawn on f5 is hanging, and Black cannot give a check on d4 with the bishop. }
14... g6 15. Be3 Bf6
{ Black improves the position and prepares to capture on f4 to clear the e5-square for the knight. }
16. Rc1
{ An optimal formation for White. The e3-bishop and the c1-rook are now well-placed for preparing c4-c5. }
16... exf4 17. Bxf4 Be5
{ Black solved all the problems and is ready to equalize by taking on f4. } *

