{ Imagine the face of someone who has never seen this idea and has to deal with it over the board! }
11... f6 { An ugly but safe move.  11...Bxg5?  loses at once. } 12. Bd2 O-O 13.
Bb4 { Adding pressure on d6. } 13... Qd7 14. Bd3 b6 15. O-O f5
{ Preparing ...e4 and taking more space.   We should also note that  15...Bb7?  fails to  16.Nxd6!  a5  17.Bf5  axb4  18.Qh3+-  , with a double  attack on d7 and h7. }
16. Rfe1 e4 17. Bf1 Bb7
{ The d5-pawn can be a target, and now that the rook is protected, White is forced to go back with the knight. }
18. Nd4 Bxd5
{ Black has an extra pawn and the center, but White has a small compensation, so Black has a tiny edge. }
*

