{ I prefer to postpone castling.  10...O-O  11.Be3  Nd7  12.Qd2  Nf6  13.f3  a6  14.Nc3  b5  15.Ne4  Nxe4  16.fxe4  Bh4+  17.Kd1  f6  18.a4  bxa4  19.Rxa4  Bg5  20.Ra3  Rb8  21.Kc1  a5  22.Bd3  Bd7  23.h4  Bxe3  24.Qxe3  a4  25.c3  Qc7  26.Bc2  Qb7  27.Ra2  Bb5  28.Kd2  Ra8  29.Rga1  Bd7  30.Bd1  h5  31.gxh5  f5  32.h6  fxe4  33.Qxe4  Rf2+  34.Kc1  Raf8  35.Qg6  R8f7  36.b4  R2f6  37.Qd3  Bb5  38.Qe3  Qxd5  39.Rd2  Qc6  40.Bc2  Rf3  41.Qe4  Qxc3  42.Qa8+  Rf8  43.Qd5+  Kh8  44.hxg7+  Kxg7  45.Qb7+  R3f7  0-1 Van Foreest-MVL Bundesliga, Germany 2022. }
11. Nc3 Nd7 12. Be3
{ White is setting a setup similar to the English Attack against the Najdorf. }
12... b5 13. Qd2 Nf6 { Forcing White to defend g4. } 14. f3 b4
{ Without castling included, Black can directly play on the queenside and doesn't give White any information about our king. }
15. Ne4 Nxe4 16. fxe4 Bh4+ 17. Kd1
{ Like in Van Foreest's game, I'd be worried about White's king. It is hard to play like this, even though it is the engine's top choice. }
17... a5 { Black keeps the king in the center and has a comfortable game. } *

