13. Be2 { In another game, White went for the quiet Be2 instead of Bxd6. }
13... a6 14. Nxd6 Qc7
{ Here's the trap! The bishop on b4 is unprotected and Black is gaining material. }
15. Nxc8 Bxb4+ { The start of a series of forcing moves. } 16. c3 Bxc3+ 17.
bxc3 Qxc3+ 18. Kf1 Raxc8
{ Black has an extra pawn, the pieces are all well-coordinated, while White cannot castle anymore. Black has a considerable advantage. }
