{ Freeing the diagonal for the queen.  In the game, Black missed this opportunity and, in the end, lost.   18...Qd6?  19.Be2  Qb4+  20.Kf1  Qc3  21.g3  Ne4  22.fxe4  f5  23.Kg2  fxe4  24.Rf1  Rxf1  25.Bxf1  Qb2+  26.Kh1  Rf8  27.Qb1  Qd4  28.Ra2  h5  29.Qe1  h4  30.gxh4  bxc4  31.Bxc4  Rf2  32.d6+  Kh8  33.Rxf2  exf2  34.Qe2  g6  35.Kg2  e3  36.Qf3  Qxd6  37.Qa8+  Kg7  38.Qxa7+  Kh8  39.Qxe3  g5  40.Qe8+  Kg7  41.Qg8+  Kh6  42.Qe6+  1-0 Lee-Eswaran, USA-ch @@StartBracket@@Women@@EndBracket@@ Saint Louis 2022. }
19. Be2 Qg5 20. g3 Nc3 21. Qc1 b4
{ The material is equal, but White's king is still in the center, and Black has an excellent outpost for the knight. So Black is winning. }
