16... a5 { Securing the c5-square for the knight. } 17. Re1
{ In an OTB game, I wouldn't play Re1 because the rook on f1 looks too good, pressing on f5. }
17... b6 { Preparing ...Ba6. } 18. Bd3 Ba6
{ Black wants to get rid of the knight on c4, but there are many things to calculate in this position. }
19. Nxb6 Nxd3 { An excellent intermediate move to simplify the position. } 20.
cxd3 Bg5
{ The line's key is that White cannot take on a8 due to ...Bxf4, and then the knight is trapped. }
21. Nxa8 Bxf4 22. Qf3 Bg5
{ Black will capture on a8 and win the game thanks to the bishop pair versus the rook. }
