{ Another greedy move. } 13... Bb7
{ In these lines with @@StartFEN@@r1bqk2r/5pbp/p1np1p2/1p1Np3/4P3/N7/PPP2PPP/R2QKB1R w KQkq - 2 11@@EndFEN@@  11.c4  , the bishop must go  to b7. }
14. Ne3 axb5
{ One of the few cases where Black quickly recaptures the pawn on b5. } 15.
Bxb5+ Kf8 { The black king usually goes to f8 or h8 in these positions. } 16.
O-O Rg8 { The start of the attack on the kingside. } 17. Qh5
{ The only move if White doesn't want to be a lot worse. It is necessary to prevent ...Qh4. }
17... Bf6 { Preparing ...Rg5. } 18. Rfc1
{ 18.Qxh7?  Now Black can go wild in the attack.  18...Nf3+  19.Kh1  Rh8-+  , the queen is trapped and White is lost. }
18... Rg5 { Waiting for White to fall into the net after Qxh7. } 19. Qxh7 Bf3
{ An excellent and visually appealing resource, threatening ...Rh5! } 20. Qh6+
{ 20.Qh3  Rh5  21.Qg3  Bh4-+  , Black traps the queen and wins the game. }
20... Bg7 21. Qh3 Rh5 22. Qg3 { Apparently, escaping from the attacks. } 22...
e4 { The white queen has a short life. } 23. Nac2
{ The engine's choice, but I would never think about that. } 23... Rg5
{ The natural  23...Be5?!  is not convincing due to a queen sacrifice with Nxd4. After  24.Nxd4  Bxg3  25.hxg3  Qf6  26.gxf3  Qxd4  27.Bc6  , White has two minor pieces and three pawns for the queen, so it is enough to have compensation @@StartBracket@@e4 is also falling next@@EndBracket@@. }
24. Qh3 Nxb5
{ One of the essential abilities in chess is to switch plans or mindsets. Beginners are often too focused on one specific thing and tend to lose sight of the big picture. Here, Black is trying to trap the opponent's queen, but if White defends well, Black can still pick up another piece instead @@StartBracket@@like the bishop on b5 in this position@@EndBracket@@.  I often tell my students that the important thing is not to give mate at all costs, but it's helpful to divert the opponent’s attention from other parts of the board, and that’s where we have to punch. Black remains with an extra minor piece and better coordination, so the advantage is enormous. }
