17. Qh3
{ Until the black king is on e8, the d3-bishop will not be hanging because of the skewer with Re1.   After other moves such as  17.Be2  or  17.Rae1  , we can just continue our plan with the same  17...Rb6  followed  by ...Rh6, ....O-O, or ...Rg8 since the king will find shelter on f8; it all depends on how White will react, but Black enjoys the upper hand. }
17... Rb6 18. Bxe4 { This doesn't work because of the intermediate ...Rh6. }
18... Rh6 { The start of some complications. } 19. Qg3 Be5 20. f4 Rg6 21. Qh3
Qc5+ { Defending the bishop on c8. } 22. Kh1 fxe4 23. Qh5 Bf6
{ Black has an extra piece, and even though White has two pawns, there is no compensation. }
