{ Black is winning. If White tries to prevent the ...d3 threat by playing  25.a7  Rbd8  26.Bd1  , after  26...Rg5  27.Qh3  Qb4  , the  position is almost resignable since ...Rdg8 comes next, while the knight on b5 is hanging too.   In case of  25.g3  d3  26.Bxd3  exd3  27.f6  , now Black has a beautiful tactical blow:  27...Bxg3!  @@StartBracket@@the queen is taboo due to mate in 2@@EndBracket@@  28.hxg3  Qd7  29.Nc3  Qc6  and White must shed material soon. }
