{ A computer move to defend d5. Other attempts fail immediately:  19.Be3  runs into  19...Rd8  followed by ...Bd3 or ...Nd4, with a winning position, and if  @@StartFEN@@r3k2r/5p1p/p1nq4/1p1Bpb2/8/6P1/P2B1P1P/R2QK2R w KQkq - 1 19@@EndFEN@@  19.Ba5  instead, the cold-blooded  19...Ke7  will put an end to White's dreams of equalizing. A rook comes to d8 next or the bishop on a5 drops, so White is forced to play  20.Bxc6  Qxc6  21.f3  , when Black is spoiled for choice. We can  sacrifice an exchange on d8 or continue with  21...Rhc8  , with a better position. }
