{ 23.Ke2??  Rd2+  24.Kf3  Qh1+  25.Kg4  Rxf2-+  and Black is winning. } 23...
Qxd1+ 24. Ke3 Qxc2 25. Bd7 Qd1
{ With good chances; ...Rb8 is a big threat and the only way to not lose the game is  26.Qg4  Qc1+  27.Kf3  , when we can play for more than a perpetual. After  27...h5  28.Qf5  Qh1+  29.Ke2  Rb8  , White has to find an only move again:  30.Bb5   30.Ra2  fails to  30...g6!  31.Qf3  Qb1  32.Rd2  Rb3  33.Qg2  Qc1  34.Rd1  , what else?  34...Qc2+  35.Ke1  Re3+  , with a winning position for Black.  30...Qb1  31.Qd7  Rxb5  32.Ra8+  Rb8  33.Rxb8+  Qxb8  , this is the maximum White can get with perfect play: being on the worse side of the endgame. }
