14... a5
{ 14...Kh8  was inspired by Giri-Carlsen ½-½ 2019.  15.Ncb4  Nxb4  16.Nxb4  Qb6  17.a4  bxa4  18.Qxa4  Bb7  19.Nxa6  Bxa6  20.Qxa6  Qxb2  21.Ra2  Qxc3  22.Qxd6  Rfd8  23.Qa3  Qd4  24.Qa7  f6  25.Qxd4  Rxd4  26.Bf3  g6  27.g3  Rb7  28.Kg2  Kg7  29.h4  Bh6  30.Rfa1  Rdb4  ½-½ Tomashevskaya-Gueci, Skopje 2019. }
15. b4
{ It never happened in my games, so I consider it a bit strange. The idea is to stop Black's ...b4 and hit on the b5-pawn with a4. }
15... Be6 16. a4
{ Played by Polina Shuvalova against Matlakov in 2021. White puts pressure on the queenside. }
16... bxa4
{ The only reasonable choice: Black cannot allow the opponent to take on b5. }
17. Rxa4 axb4 18. cxb4 { White has a passed pawn, but it is hard to push it. }
18... Ne7 { Black must contest the dominance over d5. } 19. Nxe7+ Qxe7 20. b5
Qb7
{ Black has the bishop pair and will block the strong pawn on b5 with ...Bd8-b6. There are equal chances. }
