15... Be6
{ Black is not afraid of the doubled pawns if White takes on e6 and is even happy about the structural change because it drastically solves the problem with the light squares and opens the file for the rook. }
16. Nce3 g6 { Preventing Nf5 and preparing a future ...f5 push. } 17. a4 b4
{ A typical reaction, Black prefers to open the b-file rather than the a-file. }
18. Bxe6 fxe6
{ It looks like White is losing a piece. Unfortunately, that isn't the case. }
19. Nc4 { White benefits of the unprotected knight on c6. } 19... bxc3 20. bxc3
Nd4 { An unexpected 'countertactic' to take the white knight next. } 21. cxd4
exd5 22. exd5 Rf4
