19. O-O Qc8
{ Going away with the queen from the same file as the opponent's rook. Black can improve it by putting it on c5. }
20. Nxe7+ Bxe7 21. Nf5 { Attacking both the bishop and the pawn. } 21... Qc7
22. Qg3 Bg5 { Black avoids getting mated. } 23. Nxd6 Bf4
{ Black sacrifices the weak pawn. } 24. Qf3 g6
{ White has only one unclear move, not to be worse. } 25. hxg6 fxg6
{ White's queen is in trouble. } 26. Qd3 Rbd8 { With a crushing initiative. } *

