{ GM Gelfand played ...Qh4, but ...a4 is a better choice.   19...Qh4  20.Qe1  Qxe1  21.Raxe1  Ra7  22.e5  dxe5  23.Nf6+  Kg7  24.Bxc6  Kxf6  25.fxe5+  Kg7  26.Nd4  Rc8  27.Bd5  Bxd5+  28.cxd5  Bd2  29.Re2  Bc3  30.Nc6  Rd7  31.e6  fxe6  32.dxe6  Rdc7  33.Nxa5  Re7  34.Rf3  Rce8  35.Rfe3  Kf6  36.Rf3+  Kg7  37.Rfe3  Kf6  38.Rf3+  ½-½ Esipenko-Gelfand, Moscow rapid 2018. }
20. Qe1 axb3 21. axb3 Rxa1
{ Black moves away the white queen from the kingside. } 22. Qxa1 Qh4
{ The engine says it is equal, but it is a complex position where everything can happen. }
