16. O-O { By far the most popular continuation. } 16... h5
{ Black starts to attack the kingside. } 17. h4
{ I'd play h4 with White to stop Black's expansion. } 17... Be6 18. Qxd6
{ This is usually met by ...Rac8 followed by ...Rfd8. } 18... Rac8 19. Ne3 Rfd8
20. Qc5 Nd4 21. Qb6 Rc6
{ After  22.Qxa5  Bxc4  23.Nxc4  Rxc4  ,  the knight on d4 is much stronger than the bishop on g2, and Black is still better despite being a pawn down because of the very good attacking chances on the kingside. }
