1. exd5 { This gives Black the possibility to push ...f5 directly. } 1... f5
{ Threatening ...e4 followed by ...Bxb2. The bishop finally comes into the game. }
2. cxb5 e4
{ The dark-squared bishop is more than happy now that its path is free. White cannot save both the bishop and b2. }
3. Be2 Bxb2 4. Nc4 Bc3+
{ The relative value of the rook on a1 is lower than that of the dark-squared bishop, so Black prefers to keep it for the moment and attack the king. }
5. Nd2 Bxa1 6. Qxa1 O-O
{ The material advantage gives Black a winning middlegame. } *

