{ White's king is very exposed, but the knight on e3 is a great defender. Are there other issues in the enemy's position? How do we exploit the initiative? }
1... Nf3+
{ If you have the intuition that there must be something direct, then you should examine first checks and captures, such as GM Shankland teaches in his course about calculation. The g2-pawn is pinned, so the white king is forced to go to h1.   1...Rh8-+  snares the white queen too. }
