[SetUp "1"]

{ White made a mistake with Qb3; how can we punish it? } 1... Qg5
{ Even if the position seems quiet, remember that in the Sveshnikov, there can be dynamic motifs at any time. Black threatens ...Qxg2# and forces White to weaken the king with g3. }
2. g3
{ Now that the long diagonal is free, Black must focus on finding potential tactics on the light squares. }
2... Qg4 { With the idea of ...Qf3 and mate next. } 3. f3 Bxf3
{ White escapes mate but loses a pawn, leaving Black with a considerable advantage. }
