[White "Thematic Tactics"]
[Black "Mating ideas"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "1r2r1k1/1b2qp2/p2p4/1p3P1Q/2Pb4/N2B1p2/PP4PP/4RR1K w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]

1. Rxe7
{ This is one of the craziest positions that may occur in lines with 9.Bxf6. Black is already slightly better; it looks like Black blundered and lost the queen, but there's a good-looking mate in the air. The white king is exposed thanks to the black bishop pair. }
1... fxg2# { Black punishes White's greediness. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Thematic Tactics"]
[Black "Discovered attack"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "6k1/7p/p1Bpb3/1p2b3/5r1q/2P5/PP3P1P/R2Q1R1K b - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ White has an extra exchange, but Black has the bishop pair. Both kings are exposed; which one will be mated first? }
1... Rd4
{ A discovered attack wins the game. White has to choose between losing the queen or being mated. This happens thanks to the Black's coordination on the dark squares, mainly h2. }
2. Rg1+
{ This prolongs White's suffering.   2.f4  Rxd1  3.Raxd1  Bxf4-+  and Black has a decisive material advantage. }
2... Kh8 3. Rg3 { White avoids ...Qxh2# but loses the queen. } 3... Rxd1+ 4.
Rxd1 Bxg3 5. fxg3 Qc4 *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Thematic Tactics"]
[Black "Sabotating the opponent's tactics"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r1bqk1r1/4bp1p/P7/3pp3/3nPp2/N7/PP1B1PPP/R2QKB1R w KQq - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]

1. Bxf4
{ This looks tempting, but White cannot go for tactics without developing the pieces first. }
1... Qb6
{ Black defends the knight and is ready to capture b2 and attack the dark squares. }
2. Bc1
{ White avoids both ...Qxb2 and ...exf4, but opening the fourth rank with Bxf4 favors Black since we have the strong ...Rg4 here.   After  2.Bxe5  Bb4+  ,  the king cannot escape, and the white queen is lost:  3.Qd2  Bxd2+  4.Kxd2  Qxb2+-+  . }
2... Rg4 3. f3 Rxg2
{ Stunning! Black eliminates the g-pawn to play ...Bh4+ and avoids the possibility to interpose with g3. }
4. Bxg2 Bh4+ { Mate is unavoidable. } 5. Kd2
{ 5.Kf1  leads to a good-looking end of the game.  5...Bxa6+  6.Nc4  Bxc4+  7.Qd3  Bxd3+  8.Kg1  Nxf3  . }
5... Qb4+ 6. Ke3 Bxa6 { ...Nf5+ and ...Qf4# are coming next. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Thematic Tactics"]
[Black "Clearance pawn sacrifice"]
[Result "*"]
