[SetUp "1"]

1. Bf2 { White's best option was Ke2. } 1... Bxf2+ 2. Kxf2 Qb6+
{ The white king is in trouble. } 3. Ke2 e4
{ A pivotal idea is to clear the king's diagonal and destroy the opponent's shield. }
4. Qd2 { After  4.fxe4  Bg4+-+  ,  the skewer wins the queen and the game. }
4... exf3+ 5. Ke1
{ 5.Kxf3??  Can you find a mate in five?  5...Bg4+  6.Ke4  @@StartBracket@@  6.Kg3  Be2+  7.Kh4  Qh6  @@EndBracket@@ @@StartFEN@@r3k1r1/5p1p/pq6/1p1P4/1nP1KPb1/N7/PP1Q3P/R4B1R b q - 2 6@@EndFEN@@  6...f5+  7.Ke5  Kf7  ,  threatening both ...Qf6# and ...Re8#.  8.Qxb4  Qf6  . }
5... Ra7
{ Thanks to the exposed king, Black is winning. The knight on b4 will be sacrificed to enter the enemy's half of the board with ...Re7+ and ...Rg1. }
