[SetUp "1"]

1. Qxd6
{ The difference with the previous position is that the white bishop is on f1 rather than g2, so the f3-square is weak, and Black has another trump card! }
1... Qf3 { Exploiting the opponent's lack of coordination. } 2. Rh2
{ 2.Qxc6  Qxh1-+  wins the exchange. } 2... Qxe4+
{ If the e4-pawn falls, so does White's army. } 3. Ne3 Nd4
{ Black's initiative is overpowering. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Thematic Tactics"]
[Black "Initiative compensates material"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "3r2k1/5p2/5Rp1/4n3/pRb1P3/6Pp/PP5P/6KB w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]

1. Rxa4
{ Black has enough compensation for the exchange thanks to the back-rank ideas and the poor white bishop on h1. If White lowers the guard, we will immediately punish it. }
1... Rd1+ 2. Kf2 { Black is spoiled for choice. } 2... Rxh1
{ This is the engine's favorite because it keeps the threat of ...Ng4 and prepares to promote the pawn with ...Rxh2+, ...Rxb2, and ...h2-h1. }
3. Rd6 Rxh2+ 4. Ke3 Re2+ 5. Kd4 h2 { The pawn is unstoppable and Black wins. }
