{ Let's conclude with my best result. I didn't analyze it in the Model Games chapter because I didn't play well. I had a losing position all the time and ultimately found a winning combination.  White has just blundered with Qa6; how to finish the game? If you remember the Uzbek IM who was watching the previous game, you have to know that he was watching this one too, and was shocked I didn't play this mate in three with one second on the clock. }
1... Bh3
{ Exploiting White's lack of defenders.   1...Bf5??  Watching my time going down, I made a horrible move.  2.Qe2??  My opponent has returned the favor.   After  2.Bxf2+-  , Black has no more attack and is completely hopeless.  2...Bg4?  @@StartBracket@@The best choice was:  2...Be4!!  3.Qxf2  @@StartBracket@@  3.Bxe4  Qg1+  ,  the same idea of the main line.  4.Rxg1+  Rxg1  , and if @@StartFEN@@5rk1/P6p/1N1p4/3P2q1/3Bb3/8/4QpBP/2r2R1K w - - 3 3@@EndFEN@@  3.Qxe4  Rxf1+  4.Bxf1  Qg1  @@EndBracket@@ @@StartFEN@@5rk1/P6p/1N1p4/3P2q1/3Bb3/8/5QBP/2r2R1K b - - 0 3@@EndFEN@@  3...Rxf1+  4.Qxf1  Rxf1+  5.Bg1  Bxg2  @@EndBracket@@ @@StartFEN@@5rk1/P6p/1N1p4/3P2q1/3B2b1/8/4QpBP/2r2R1K w - - 3 3@@EndFEN@@  3.Qxf2  Rxf1+  4.Bxf1  Rxf2  5.a8=Q+  Rf8  and my opponent resigned because of ...Bf3+ or ...Rxf1. }
2. Bxh3 { 2.a8=Q  Qxg2 } 2... Qg1+
{ I was so tired that I thought that after  3.Rxg1+  fxg1=Q+  , there's  4.Bxg1  and White wins.  But after Rxg1+, Black has a mate in 1. }
3. Rxg1+ Rxg1#
{ This is the end of the course. I hope you liked it and chose the Sveshnikov as your principal weapon. }
